<P>
Japanese Buying More Imported Cars: Fed by a strong appetite for luxury cars, 
import sales in Japan surged 10.2% from a year earlier to 15,435 vehicles in 
August, the Japanese Automobile Importers Assn. said. 
</P>
<P>
August sales were down from 20,304 in July. West German makers accounted for 
8,736, or over half the imports in the month. Sales of U.S. car makers surged 
35.7%. General Motors Corp. sold 685 vehicles, up 5.2% from a year earlier. 
Ford Motor Co. sales dipped 29.2% to 286, but Chrysler Corp. vehicles posted a 
58.6% advance to 111. 
</P>
